 Mary. It is also borne by a rich Jew, Joseph of Arimathea (Matthew 27:57; Mark 15:43; Luke 23:50; John 19:38), who took Jesus down from the Cross, wrapped him in a shroud, and buried him in a rock tomb. According to medieval legend, Joseph of Arimathea brought the Holy Grail to Britain. The name was uncommon in Britain in the Middle Ages but was revived in the mid 16th century and had become popular by the 1630s, remaining so ever since."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":45,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":54,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Jobe Cox was born in 1170, in Ely, Cambridgeshire, England, his father, Francis Cox, was 23 and his mother, Jane, was 20. He married Sarah Doggett about 1194, in Ely, Cambridgeshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1232, in his hometown, at the age of 62."},"et":{"1170–1232":"1170–1232","1175–1236":"1175–1236","1195–Male":"1195–Surnud","1200–1275":"1200–1275","1147–1217":"1147–1217","1150–1218":"1150–1218","about 1194":"umbes 1194","about 1195":"umbes 1195","1275":"1275","1175":"1175","1195":"1195","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1217":"1217","1215":"1215","1236":"1236","1224":"1224","1147":"1147","1200":"1200","1232":"1232","about 1169":"umbes 1169","1218":"1218","Ely, Camb